From: Egbert Eich <Egbert Eich eich@suse.de>
Date: Mon May 6 17:43:17 2013 +0200
Subject: drm/mgag200: Initialize data needed to map fbdev memory.
Patch-Mainline: to be upstreamed
Git-commit: 183e13c97ce13758bf13580ffecd2aa90e5c930e
Git-repo: git://people.freedesktop.org/~airlied/linux/
References: bnc #806990
Signed-off-by: Egbert Eich <eich@suse.com>

Due to a missing initialization there was no way to map fbdev memory.
Thus for example using the Xserver with the fbdev driver failed.
This fix adds initialization for fix.smem_start and fix.smem_len
in the fb_info structure, which fixes this problem.

Signed-off-by: Egbert Eich <eich@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/mgag200/mgag200_drv.h  |    1 +
 drivers/gpu/drm/mgag200/mgag200_fb.c   |    7 +++++++
 drivers/gpu/drm/mgag200/mgag200_mode.c |    3 ++-
 3 files changed, 10 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- linux-3.0-SLE11-SP3.orig/drivers/gpu/drm/mgag200/mgag200_fb.c
+++ linux-3.0-SLE11-SP3/drivers/gpu/drm/mgag200/mgag200_fb.c
@@ -302,3 +302,10 @@ void mgag200_fbdev_fini(struct mga_devic
 	kfree(mdev->mfbdev);
 	mdev->mfbdev = NULL;
 }
+
+void mgag200_fbdev_set_base(struct mga_device *mdev, unsigned long gpu_addr)
+{
+	mdev->mfbdev->helper.fbdev->fix.smem_start =
+		mdev->mfbdev->helper.fbdev->apertures->ranges[0].base + gpu_addr;
+	mdev->mfbdev->helper.fbdev->fix.smem_len = mdev->mc.vram_size - gpu_addr;
+}
--- linux-3.0-SLE11-SP3.orig/drivers/gpu/drm/mgag200/mgag200_drv.h
+++ linux-3.0-SLE11-SP3/drivers/gpu/drm/mgag200/mgag200_drv.h
@@ -230,6 +230,7 @@ void mgag200_modeset_fini(struct mga_dev
 				/* mga_fbdev.c */
 int mgag200_fbdev_init(struct mga_device *mdev);
 void mgag200_fbdev_fini(struct mga_device *mdev);
+void mgag200_fbdev_set_base(struct mga_device *mdev, unsigned long gpu_addr);
 
 				/* mgag200_main.c */
 int mgag200_framebuffer_init(struct drm_device *dev,
--- linux-3.0-SLE11-SP3.orig/drivers/gpu/drm/mgag200/mgag200_mode.c
+++ linux-3.0-SLE11-SP3/drivers/gpu/drm/mgag200/mgag200_mode.c
@@ -743,7 +743,8 @@ static int mga_crtc_do_set_base(struct d
 		ret = ttm_bo_kmap(&bo->bo, 0, bo->bo.num_pages, &bo->kmap);
 		if (ret)
 			DRM_ERROR("failed to kmap fbcon\n");
-
+		else
+			mgag200_fbdev_set_base(mdev, gpu_addr);
 	}
 	mgag200_bo_unreserve(bo);
 
